A characteristic of CUT&RUN protocols is that the amount of DNA recovered at this step is very low and even sensitive methods provide unreliable concentration numbers. For a typical transcription factor subjected to greenCUT&RUN, DNA concentrations will be in the range of 1-5 ng/µl, while for the no GFP or no Ca++ control, it will be ∼1 ng/µl. For GFP-tagged histone proteins, DNA concentrations range between 20 and 120 ng/µl.
48. Prepare sequencing libraries using 0.5-10 ng of DNA and the NEBNext Ultra II library prep kit for Illumina from New England Biolabs following the manufacturer's instructions. In order to increase recovery of small fragments, however, implement the following modifications:

omit the size selection step to prevent the loss of small DNA fragments, which are the major contributor to high-spatial resolutions by CUT&RUN mapping methods;
reduce the temperature and increase the incubation time of enzyme inactivation of the End Prep step of the NEBNext Ultra II protocol from 30 min at 65°C to 60 min at 50°C. This reduces the denaturation of small DNA fragments, which increases the efficiency of adaptor ligation to small DNA fragments;
reduce the annealing/extension time of the PCR amplification step from 75 s at 65°C to 10 s at 65°C.
